### Updating a form after publication

You can update a form in settings. The live form will continue collecting responses until you publish the update.

### Test your form before updating

Non-developers may need to check with developers before editing the form. You may need to:
- Adjust form questions and workflows.
- Revise lists and spreadsheets for organizing responses. 
- Update API integration.

### After you publish

The earlier version remains in our database. But you’ll no longer be able to view it.

New form fillers only have access to the updated form. People mid-way through the previous form can complete the earlier version unless they reload the page. 
